<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 18 at 3:00PM MDT until August 18 at 3:30PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 PM MDT
FOR EASTERN MADISON AND SOUTHEASTERN BEAVERHEAD COUNTIES...
At 259 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 10 miles south of Ennis to 15 miles north of Kilgore,
moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Ennis, Norris, Mcallister, Lakeview, Jeffers, Cameron, Raynolds Pass
and Red Rock Pass.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
